data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

In EF Core 11, the **sync-over-async opt-in for the Cosmos DB provider is removed entirely**. The `CosmosEventId.SyncNotSupported` suppression you configured in .NET 10 no longer has any effect.

All synchronous LINQ operators (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`) and `SaveChanges()` on the Cosmos provider will throw an **`InvalidOperationException`** at runtime — with no workaround.

## The fix: convert to async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key changes:**
- `ToList()` → `ToListAsync()` / `First()` → `FirstAsync()` / `Count()` → `CountAsync()`
- `SaveChanges()` → `SaveChangesAsync()`
- Return types become `Task<T>` / `Task`
- Callers must be updated to `await` these methods

You can also remove the `CosmosEventId.SyncNotSupported` suppression from your `DbContext` configuration — it's dead code now.
